data.description:
Newcomer was asked to develop a small but separate and independed module of an application.
Task was just to create a `simpleConfig` function for an application config creation. That config object accepts default value for nonexisting keys, also it has two methods `get` and `set`, which just set properties values and get those values back.  

Following is example how this object could be used propely:

```javascript
const config = simpleConfig('default value');
config.set('some', 'value');
console.log(config.get('some'));
console.log(config.get('non_existing_key'));
```
As you see it just a wrapper on an object which returns default value for non existing keys.

But we know that it has a bug, please find it and fix it.
Unfortunatly we lost all errored test cases, you need to find incorrect behavior before fixing.
